Introduction

Information security is an important field in computer science. One of the oldest and simplest encryption methods is the Caesar Cipher, which was used to protect secret messages by shifting letters in the alphabet. This project presents a simple C++ program that encodes and decodes messages using this technique.
Project Objectives
The objectives of this project are:
To understand the basic concept of encryption and decryption.
To apply the Caesar Cipher algorithm in C++.
To practice using strings, loops, and conditional statements.
To correctly handle user input and output.
Description of the Caesar Cipher
The Caesar Cipher is based on shifting letters by a fixed number called the shift key.
Encoding shifts letters forward in the alphabet.
Decoding shifts letters backward using the same key.
Uppercase letters remain uppercase.
Lowercase letters remain lowercase.
Non-alphabetic characters such as spaces, numbers, and symbols are not modified.

